Package neupaths.api

Class LogicMapSubscriptionSpec

java.lang.Object
neupaths.api.SubscriptionSpec
neupaths.api.LogicSubscriptionSpec
neupaths.api.LogicMapSubscriptionSpec
public final class LogicMapSubscriptionSpec extends LogicSubscriptionSpec
Map subscription specification for LogicCells. An activator can request that stimuli from a specified transmitter be placed on a receptor with the same (or matching) name. A map subscription is composed of the following:
  • Cell Name - The name of the cell or injector that created the stimulus. This value may contain a regular expression.
  • Transmitter Name - The name of the transmitter that sent the stimulus. This value may contain a regular expression.
  • Domain - The domain in which the stimulus will be processed.
  • Filter Transactions - For stimuli that are service responses, indicates if redundant responses should be filtered.

Filter Transactions specifies whether the extractor cell should filter redundant service responses for a given transaction ID. This is useful when multiple cells are servicing the same transaction.
